27 prison for life with eligibility for parole beginning when a minimum of 10 years has
28 been served, and by a fine of not more than $20,000.
29 Existing law makes the crime of facilitating sex trafficking of a victim who is
30 less than 18 years of age a category B felony, punishable by imprisonment in the
31 state prison for a minimum term of not less than 3 years and a maximum term of
32 not more than 10 years. (NRS 201.301) Section 2 of this bill increases the
33 punishment for such a crime to imprisonment in the state prison for a minimum
34 term of 8 years and a maximum term of 20 years.
