17 maintains a person by any means, knowing, or in reckless disregard
18 of the fact, that threats, violence, force, intimidation, fraud, duress
19 or coercion will be used to cause the person to engage in
20 prostitution, or to enter any place within this State in which
21 prostitution is practiced, encouraged or allowed for the purpose of
22 sexual conduct or prostitution;
23 (3) By threats, violence, force, intimidation, fraud, duress,
24 coercion, by any device or scheme, or by abuse of any position of
25 confidence or authority, or having legal charge, takes, places,
26 harbors, induces, causes, compels or procures a person to engage in
27 prostitution, or to enter any place within this State in which
28 prostitution is practiced, encouraged or allowed for the purpose of
29 sexual conduct or prostitution;
30 (4) Takes or detains a person with the intent to compel the
31 person by force, violence, threats or duress to marry him or her or
32 any other person; or
33 (5) Receives anything of value with the specific intent of
34 facilitating a violation of this paragraph.
